description:
&lt;p&gt;East Cheshire NHS Trust NEEDS YOU!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you passionate about care ?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working 24 hours/week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;If you are passionate about excellent patient care and have the skills and experience to work within community nursing, this is the role for you!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;East Cheshire NHS Trust provides high quality community care for people in their own homes and some clinic environments. The service covers patients living in Congleton and Holmes Chapel locations and you will be based with the community nursing team at Congleton War Memorial Hospital but will be expected to cover Holmes Chapel dependant on service needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have the relevant qualifications, skills and experience, car driver or evidence of how you could travel and want to support us in providing excellent care for our patients please apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is Permanent&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hours per week: 24&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 15th November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please be aware that this post requires an Enhanced with Barred list Disclosure and Barring Service (DBS) check, the cost of which is payable by the successful candidate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you have lived or worked abroad for 6 months or more in the last 5 years you will need to obtain an overseas police clearance. Further information can be found on the additional information links at the bottom of the advert.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;To keep up to date with all of our latest Recruitment activity here at East Cheshire NHS Trust, take a look at our Careers website with lots of information on how to join our team and Facebook and Twitter pages, links to which can be found on the right hand side:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Visit our Facebook page: Careers at East Cheshire NHS Trust&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Follow us on Twitter: @CareersECT&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name Emily Bourne Job title Team Leader Email address emily.bourne1@nhs.net Telephone number 0300 3230223&lt;/p&gt;
